================================================================================
WHICH OPTION APPLIES TO YOU?
================================================================================

You are using Kaption under AGPL-3.0 if any of the following are true:

  * You install and run the official binary for personal use
  * You build from source for personal use, evaluation, or security
    research
  * You publish a fork (under a different name) on GitHub, GitLab, etc.,
    under AGPL-3.0 with full source available
  * You contribute fixes or features back via pull requests

You need a commercial licence if any of the following are true:

  * You want to ship a closed-source product or service that includes
    Kaption code
  * You cannot or will not release your derivative work under AGPL-3.0
  * You need a contractual warranty, SLA, indemnity, or formal support

When in doubt, contact us — we will tell you which one applies and we
do not charge for the conversation.

  Email:   hello@kaption.one
  Website: https://kaption.one

